<td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_05.gif" class="headerbg"><font class="h1font"><font color="#FFFFFF"><table cellspacing=0 cellpadding=0 border=0 width=100%><TR><td><font class="h1font">Articles</td><form method='post' action=''><input type="hidden" name="PHPSESSID" value="...328fedb22570524062aeb1303" /><td align='right' valign='bottom'><select name='select' onChange='go(this)'><option selected>More DeckTech Articles</option><option value='#'> </option><option value='/starwarsccg/articles/index.php3'>Star Wars: CCG</option><option value='/vs/articles/index.php3'>Marvel VS</option><option value='/heroclix/articles/articles.php'>HeroClix</option><option value='/lotr/articles/articles.php'>Lord of the Rings</option><option value='/magination/articles/articles.php'>Magi-Nation Duel</option><option value='/swtcg/articles/articles.php'>Ophidian 2350</option><option value='/magic/treports/treports.php'>The Wastelands</option></select></td></form></tr></table></font></B></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/red_06.gif"></td></tr>
	<tr><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_07.gif"></td>
		<td bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_08.gif"><font class="bfont"><font class="h1font"> Olorin the Wizard<br></font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Overall Rating:</b> </font><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><img src="/lotr/gfx/star2.gif" width="19" height="21" border="0" align="absmiddle"><font size='1'>(3.80)</font><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Author:</b> <A HREF='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=15062'>Stefanos "Stef" Kehagias</A></font><font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/lotr/main/mpage.php?member=15062&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a><br><font class="h2font"> <b>Date Submitted:</b> February 19, 2004</font><p align='justify'><font class="bfont">    In this article,my second here in Decktech I want to examine the &quot;Gandalf case&quot;.So, what&#39;s the story with this guy?Who is he?Where did he came from?What are his weeknesses and what his advantages?I believe these are in deed &quot;Questions that need answering&quot;....<br />
   Let&#39;s take a look back in time...<br />
   Erou the One who is called Ilouvatar in Arnta,created first the Ainour who were children of his thought.And they made a great music before him through which the world begun...The greater spirits among the Ainour were called Valar,Forces of Arnta by the Elfs and Men have often named them Gods.But there were also some spirits of lesser rank who existed before the days of the world.These are Maiar the people of Valar,their servants and their assistants.The number of Maiar is unknown to the Elfs and very fiew of them have names.The wisest Maia was said to be Olorin who had learned compassion and patience from Nienna one of the greatest Valar!<br />
    Olorin loved middle earth a lot and when it took it&#39;s final shape-the day Melkor was captured after the last great battle of Beleriant took place-Valar sent him to the aid of all the people of middle earth.However he took a form of an old man and he appeared to the world not as a great spirit of the west but as a helper to those who needed guidance.As you all have understood Olorin is Gandalf also known as Mithrandir.People knew him as the second of his order,the order of wizards.It is said that he arrived in Middle Earth at the beginning of the third age in a ship coming from the west.<br />
   That&#39;s enough with Tolkien.I know i skipped my point a bit but i like these kind of stuff.<br />
   I started writing this article thinking why do many newcommers like Gandalf so much.And with this thought i suddendly realised that most of my friends that originally played Gandalf decks and have changed through time their free peoples culture,they still &quot;trust him&quot; as they once did.The reason this happens is in my opinion that Gandalf  is a tool for every job.You can design any deck you like fearing nothing only because you have Gandalf.He has an answer to any problem ,to any shadow.I believe you all agree with that.Gandalf offers a great skirmish winning ability(trust me, servant...)helps with healing (Have patience)deals with Grima and Enquea allowing you to play many possesions many cultures and many companions(Terrible and evil)and of cource he is the king of condition removal.And these are only half Gandy does.His culture has the best burden removal cards(Narya Gandalf&#39;s pipe)it can be combined succesfully with almost any other culture(Last PSQ winning deck had Gandalf and Smeagol as basic companions)and has the 4 life tree companions which are not easy victims.In addition to all that there are many common Gandalf cards such as Trust me,Sleep Charadras,Gandalf the white,Deep in thought that allows a player to design a deck in a minute.After all that i don&#39;t think sth else is needed to prove Gandalf&#39;s supperiority over other cultures.<br />
   I know that all the experienced lotr tcg players will say now:We know all that.We didn&#39;t expect you to teach us...No i don&#39;t want to be the smart guy.Nor do i want to post an article that will help noone.I just want to talk about the cost this variety of Gandy&#39;s culture has.In my opinion it is not the twillight cost as many of you will think:Ok i like the 10 str 5 life companion who is def +1 or the Roll of thunder but the cost is too much so i prefer Dh.This point of view belongs to players that see the game very arithmeticly.I am also a fun of choke but I believe this opinion would make me a very narrow minded person.It is not the twillight cost.The real cost you have to pay when you play Gandy is found in the essence of the card game itself.The importance of cycling your hand and changing your gaming options is this essence.To make myself clear,i ll give an example.As much as influenced i am from the meta in Greece nobody will change my mind that Gandalf culture needs events to work.Let&#39;s say that my Fellowship is set up at site 5 and i have in my hand 4 events.My opponent passes his shadow phase.Am i or not forced by my opponent to double move?The answer is yes because if i stay my hand will have 3 useless cards provided i discard one meaning that my shadow&#39;s success is ruined.So my point here is:In a Gan. deck if your opponent passes his shadow phase your gaming options are limited and the control of the game is at your opponent&#39;s hands.This is the real cost the efficiency of Gandalf culture has.If you have any objection on that, consider how many times you have seen a Gandalf deck &quot;Dying&quot; in a single move.Or even consider how important Linderoot and Barliman are in a Gandalf deck.Linderoot to get rid of the roll the wizard the second copy of Gandalf or a possesion already in play and Barliman to bring back the roll you had to discard...<br />
   Many of the above could be written in an article that discusses the x-listing of palantir.I remember all of my friends who played Gandalf having a copy of Elrand in their deck since palantir did the same with passing a shadow phase:Ruining their gaming options.now to change the subject i ll finish my article with a comment in Gandalf&#39;s transformation.<br />
   In the begining We had the  Grey pilgrim,the good wizard who only shoed his power against the Balrog(Servant of the secret fire and when facing the rage of Charadras(Sleep Charadras).The cost of most Gandalf cards was small and there were fiew exceptions.Gandalf was there to support to help and guide the hobbits.He did exactly what he was sent to do.When the TT came up a very different wizard appeared.His spells where much more powerful and funcy at the same time.&quot;Have patience&quot;,&quot;Grown suddendly tall&quot;,&quot;Mithrandir,Mithrandir&quot; are a some examples.The cost is now much bigger.Olorin has left the role of the assistant and is now a fighter himself.Reaching to a zennith of his glory the white rider comes &quot;Down from the hill&quot; to brake the Uruk hai line out of Helm&#39;s deep!And with the arrival of Rotk he is none the less more fearless than ever.(Terrible and Evil...).What decipher did here is offering players more and more powerful cards which will allow however bigger and better shadow phases.And this is exactly what happens.The white wizard is afraid of nothing sth that explains the high t.cost of his spells.<br />
   Well i believe that&#39;s all.There are much more to say about the Great wizard but i&#39;ve already said a lot.I hope i didn&#39;t tire you.Thank you for reading my post.<br />
        <br />
